Fourth Department,

July, 1952.

(July 9,1952.) Homer L. Householder, Respondent, v. Town of Grand Island, Erie County, Appellant.

Judgment affirmed, with costs. All concur. (Appeal from a judgment for plaintiff in an action to declare a town ordinance to be unconstitutional.) Present — Taylor, P. J., MeCurn, Vaughan, Kimball and Piper, JJ. [See post, p. 910.]
